34 CConfig::CConfig(char case_filename[MAX_STRING_SIZE], unsigned short val_software, unsigned short val_iZone, unsigned short val_nZone, unsigned short val_nDim, unsigned short verb_level) {
35 
36  int rank = MASTER_NODE;
37 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
38  MPI_Comm_rank(MPI_COMM_WORLD, &rank);
39 #endif
40 
41  /*--- Initialize pointers to Null---*/
42 
43  SetPointersNull();
44 
45  /*--- Reading config options ---*/
46 
47  SetConfig_Options(val_iZone, val_nZone);
48 
49  /*--- Parsing the config file ---*/
50 
51  SetConfig_Parsing(case_filename);
52 
53  /*--- Configuration file postprocessing ---*/
54 
55  SetPostprocessing(val_software, val_iZone, val_nDim);
56 
57  /*--- Configuration file boundaries/markers setting ---*/
58 
59  SetMarkers(val_software);
60 
61  /*--- Configuration file output ---*/
62 
63  if ((rank == MASTER_NODE) && (verb_level == VERB_HIGH) && (val_iZone != 1))
64  SetOutput(val_software, val_iZone);
65 
66 }

88 CConfig::CConfig(char case_filename[MAX_STRING_SIZE], CConfig *config) {
89 
90  bool runtime_file = false;
91 
92  /*--- Initialize pointers to Null---*/
93 
94  SetPointersNull();
95 
96  /*--- Reading config options ---*/
97 
98  SetRunTime_Options();
99 
100  /*--- Parsing the config file ---*/
101 
102  runtime_file = SetRunTime_Parsing(case_filename);
103 
104  /*--- Update original config file ---*/
105 
106  if (runtime_file) {
107  config->SetnExtIter(nExtIter);
108  }

221  // This config file is parsed by a number of programs to make it easy to write SU2
222  // wrapper scripts (in python, go, etc.) so please do
223  // the best you can to follow the established format. It's very hard to parse c++ code

225  // play nice with the existing format so that you don't break the existing scripts.

540  /* !\brief CFL_ADAPT_PARAM
541  * DESCRIPTION: Parameters of the adaptive CFL number (factor down, factor up, CFL limit (min and max) )
542  * Factor down generally >1.0, factor up generally < 1.0 to cause the CFL to increase when residual is decreasing,

1428 void CConfig::SetConfig_Parsing(char case_filename[MAX_STRING_SIZE]) {
1429  string text_line, option_name;
1430  ifstream case_file;
1431  vector<string> option_value;
1432  int rank = MASTER_NODE;
1433 
1434 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
1435  MPI_Comm_rank(MPI_COMM_WORLD, &rank);
1436 #endif
1437 
1438  /*--- Read the configuration file ---*/
1439 
1440  case_file.open(case_filename, ios::in);
1441 
1442  if (case_file.fail()) {
1443  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << endl << "The configuration file (.cfg) is missing!!" << endl << endl;
1444  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
1445  }
1446 
1447  string errorString;
1448 
1449  int err_count = 0; // How many errors have we found in the config file
1450  int max_err_count = 30; // Maximum number of errors to print before stopping
1451 
1452  map<string, bool> included_options;
1453 
1454  /*--- Parse the configuration file and set the options ---*/
1455 
1456  while (getline (case_file, text_line)) {
1457 
1458  if (err_count >= max_err_count) {
1459  errorString.append("too many errors. Stopping parse");
1460 
1461  cout << errorString << endl;
1462  throw(1);
1463  }
1464 
1465  if (TokenizeString(text_line, option_name, option_value)) {
1466 
1467  /*--- See if it's a python option ---*/
1468 
1469  if (option_map.find(option_name) == option_map.end()) {
1470  string newString;
1471  newString.append(option_name);
1472  newString.append(": invalid option name");
1473  newString.append(". Check current SU2 options in config_template.cfg.");
1474  newString.append("\n");
1475  errorString.append(newString);
1476  err_count++;
1477  continue;
1478  }
1479 
1480  /*--- Option exists, check if the option has already been in the config file ---*/
1481 
1482  if (included_options.find(option_name) != included_options.end()) {
1483  string newString;
1484  newString.append(option_name);
1485  newString.append(": option appears twice");
1486  newString.append("\n");
1487  errorString.append(newString);
1488  err_count++;
1489  continue;
1490  }
1491 
1492 
1493  /*--- New found option. Add it to the map, and delete from all options ---*/
1494 
1495  included_options.insert(pair<string, bool>(option_name, true));
1496  all_options.erase(option_name);
1497 
1498  /*--- Set the value and check error ---*/
1499 
1500  string out = option_map[option_name]->SetValue(option_value);
1501  if (out.compare("") != 0) {
1502  errorString.append(out);
1503  errorString.append("\n");
1504  err_count++;
1505  }
1506  }
1507  }
1508 
1509  /*--- See if there were any errors parsing the config file ---*/
1510 
1511  if (errorString.size() != 0) {
1512  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << errorString << endl;
1513  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
1514  }
1515 
1516  /*--- Set the default values for all of the options that weren't set ---*/
1517 
1518  for (map<string, bool>::iterator iter = all_options.begin(); iter != all_options.end(); ++iter) {
1519  option_map[iter->first]->SetDefault();
1520  }
1521 
1522  case_file.close();
1523 
1524 }
1525 
1526 bool CConfig::SetRunTime_Parsing(char case_filename[MAX_STRING_SIZE]) {
1527  string text_line, option_name;
1528  ifstream case_file;
1529  vector<string> option_value;
1530  int rank = MASTER_NODE;
1531 
1532 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
1533  MPI_Comm_rank(MPI_COMM_WORLD, &rank);
1534 #endif
1535 
1536  /*--- Read the configuration file ---*/
1537 
1538  case_file.open(case_filename, ios::in);
1539 
1540  if (case_file.fail()) { return false; }
1541 
1542  string errorString;
1543 
1544  int err_count = 0; // How many errors have we found in the config file
1545  int max_err_count = 30; // Maximum number of errors to print before stopping
1546 
1547  map<string, bool> included_options;
1548 
1549  /*--- Parse the configuration file and set the options ---*/
1550 
1551  while (getline (case_file, text_line)) {
1552 
1553  if (err_count >= max_err_count) {
1554  errorString.append("too many errors. Stopping parse");
1555 
1556  cout << errorString << endl;
1557  throw(1);
1558  }
1559 
1560  if (TokenizeString(text_line, option_name, option_value)) {
1561 
1562  if (option_map.find(option_name) == option_map.end()) {
1563 
1564  /*--- See if it's a python option ---*/
1565 
1566  string newString;
1567  newString.append(option_name);
1568  newString.append(": invalid option name");
1569  newString.append("\n");
1570  errorString.append(newString);
1571  err_count++;
1572  continue;
1573  }
1574 
1575  /*--- Option exists, check if the option has already been in the config file ---*/
1576 
1577  if (included_options.find(option_name) != included_options.end()) {
1578  string newString;
1579  newString.append(option_name);
1580  newString.append(": option appears twice");
1581  newString.append("\n");
1582  errorString.append(newString);
1583  err_count++;
1584  continue;
1585  }
1586 
1587  /*--- New found option. Add it to the map, and delete from all options ---*/
1588 
1589  included_options.insert(pair<string, bool>(option_name, true));
1590  all_options.erase(option_name);
1591 
1592  /*--- Set the value and check error ---*/
1593 
1594  string out = option_map[option_name]->SetValue(option_value);
1595  if (out.compare("") != 0) {
1596  errorString.append(out);
1597  errorString.append("\n");
1598  err_count++;
1599  }
1600 
1601  }
1602  }
1603 
1604  /*--- See if there were any errors parsing the runtime file ---*/
1605 
1606  if (errorString.size() != 0) {
1607  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << errorString << endl;
1608  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
1609  }
1610 
1611  case_file.close();
1612 
1613  return true;
1614 
1615 }

1617 void CConfig::SetPostprocessing(unsigned short val_software, unsigned short val_izone, unsigned short val_nDim) {
1618 
1619  unsigned short iZone, iCFL, iDim;
1620  bool ideal_gas = (Kind_FluidModel == STANDARD_AIR || Kind_FluidModel == IDEAL_GAS );
1621  bool standard_air = (Kind_FluidModel == STANDARD_AIR);
1622 
1623 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
1624  int size = SINGLE_NODE;
1625  MPI_Comm_size(MPI_COMM_WORLD, &size);
1626 #endif
1627 
1628 #ifndef HAVE_TECIO
1629  if (Output_FileFormat == TECPLOT_BINARY) {
1630  cout << "Tecplot binary file requested but SU2 was built without TecIO support." << "\n";
1631  Output_FileFormat = TECPLOT;
1632  }
1633 #endif
1634 
1635  /*--- Store the SU2 module that we are executing. ---*/
1636 
1637  Kind_SU2 = val_software;
1638 
1639  /*--- Make sure that 1D outputs are written when objective function requires ---*/
1640 
1641  if (Kind_ObjFunc== AVG_OUTLET_PRESSURE || Kind_ObjFunc == AVG_TOTAL_PRESSURE || Kind_ObjFunc == OUTFLOW_GENERALIZED) {
1642  Wrt_1D_Output = YES;
1643  Marker_Out_1D = new string[nMarker_Monitoring];
1644  for (unsigned short iMarker=0; iMarker<nMarker_Monitoring; iMarker++){
1645  Marker_Out_1D[iMarker] = Marker_Monitoring[iMarker];
1646  }
1647  nMarker_Out_1D = nMarker_Monitoring;
1648  }
1649 
1650  /*--- Low memory only for ASCII Tecplot ---*/
1651 
1652  if (Output_FileFormat != TECPLOT) Low_MemoryOutput = NO;
1653 
1654  /*--- Deactivate the multigrid in the adjoint problem ---*/
1655 
1656  if ((ContinuousAdjoint && !MG_AdjointFlow) ||
1657  (Unsteady_Simulation == TIME_STEPPING)) { nMGLevels = 0; }
1658 
1659  /*--- If Fluid Structure Interaction, set the solver for each zone.
1660  *--- ZONE_0 is the zone of the fluid.
1661  *--- All the other zones are structure.
1662  *--- This will allow us to define multiple physics structural problems */
1663 
1664  if (Kind_Solver == FLUID_STRUCTURE_INTERACTION){
1665  if (val_izone==0) { Kind_Solver = Kind_Solver_Fluid_FSI; FSI_Problem = true;}
1666 
1667  else { Kind_Solver = Kind_Solver_Struc_FSI; FSI_Problem = true;
1668  Kind_Linear_Solver = Kind_Linear_Solver_FSI_Struc;
1669  Kind_Linear_Solver_Prec = Kind_Linear_Solver_Prec_FSI_Struc;
1670  Linear_Solver_Error = Linear_Solver_Error_FSI_Struc;
1671  Linear_Solver_Iter = Linear_Solver_Iter_FSI_Struc;}
1672  }
1673  else{ FSI_Problem = false; }
1674 
1675 
1676  /*--- Initialize non-physical points/reconstructions to zero ---*/
1677 
1678  Nonphys_Points = 0;
1679  Nonphys_Reconstr = 0;
1680 
1681  /*--- Don't do any deformation if there is no Design variable information ---*/
1682 
1683  if (Design_Variable == NULL) {
1684  Design_Variable = new unsigned short [1];
1685  nDV = 1; Design_Variable[0] = NONE;
1686  }
1687 
1688  /*--- Identification of free-surface problem, this problems are always
1689  unsteady and incompressible. ---*/
1690 
1691  if (Kind_Regime == FREESURFACE) {
1692  if (Unsteady_Simulation != DT_STEPPING_2ND) Unsteady_Simulation = DT_STEPPING_1ST;
1693  }
1694 
1695  if (Kind_Solver == POISSON_EQUATION) {
1696  Unsteady_Simulation = STEADY;
1697  }
1698 
1699  /*--- Set the number of external iterations to 1 for the steady state problem ---*/
1700 
1701  if ((Kind_Solver == HEAT_EQUATION) ||
1702  (Kind_Solver == WAVE_EQUATION) || (Kind_Solver == POISSON_EQUATION)) {
1703  nMGLevels = 0;
1704  if (Unsteady_Simulation == STEADY) nExtIter = 1;
1705  else Unst_nIntIter = 2;
1706  }
1707 
1708  if (Kind_Solver == FEM_ELASTICITY) {
1709  nMGLevels = 0;
1710  if (Dynamic_Analysis == STATIC)
1711  nExtIter = 1;
1712  }
1713 
1714  /*--- Decide whether we should be writing unsteady solution files. ---*/
1715 
1716  if (Unsteady_Simulation == STEADY ||
1717  Unsteady_Simulation == TIME_SPECTRAL ||
1718  Kind_Regime == FREESURFACE) { Wrt_Unsteady = false; }
1719  else { Wrt_Unsteady = true; }
1720 
1721  if (Kind_Solver == FEM_ELASTICITY) {
1722 
1723  if (Dynamic_Analysis == STATIC) { Wrt_Dynamic = false; }
1724  else { Wrt_Dynamic = true; }
1725 
1726  } else {
1727  Wrt_Dynamic = false;
1728  }
1729 
1730 
1731  /*--- Check for Fluid model consistency ---*/
1732 
1733  if (standard_air){
1734  if (Gamma != 1.4 || Gas_Constant != 287.058){
1735  Gamma = 1.4;
1736  Gas_Constant = 287.058;
1737  }
1738  }
1739  /*--- Check for Measurement System ---*/
1740 
1741  if (SystemMeasurements == US && !standard_air) {
1742  cout << "Only STANDARD_AIR fluid model can be used with US Measurement System" << endl;
1743  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
1744  }
1745 
1746  /*--- Check for Convective scheme available for NICFD ---*/
1747 
1748  if (!ideal_gas) {
1749  if (Kind_ConvNumScheme_Flow != SPACE_UPWIND) {
1750  cout << "Only ROE Upwind and HLLC Upwind scheme can be used for Non-Ideal Compressible Fluids" << endl;
1751  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
1752  }
1753  else {
1754  if (Kind_Upwind_Flow != ROE && Kind_Upwind_Flow != HLLC) {
1755  cout << "Only ROE Upwind and HLLC Upwind scheme can be used for Non-Ideal Compressible Fluids" << endl;
1756  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
1757  }
1758  }
1759  }
1760 
1761  /*--- Check for Boundary condition available for NICFD ---*/
1762 
1763  if (!ideal_gas) {
1764  if (nMarker_Inlet != 0) {
1765  cout << "Riemann Boundary conditions or NRBC must be used for inlet and outlet with Not Ideal Compressible Fluids " << endl;
1766  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
1767  }
1768  if (nMarker_Outlet != 0) {
1769  cout << "Riemann Boundary conditions or NRBC must be used outlet with Not Ideal Compressible Fluids " << endl;
1770  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
1771  }
1772 
1773  if (nMarker_FarField != 0) {
1774  cout << "Riemann Boundary conditions or NRBC must be used outlet with Not Ideal Compressible Fluids " << endl;
1775  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
1776  }
1777 
1778  }
1779

1781

1784  if (Kind_ViscosityModel != SUTHERLAND) {
1785  cout << "Only SUTHERLAND viscosity model can be used with US Measurement " << endl;
1786  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
1787  }
1788  }

1790  cout << "Only CONSTANT_PRANDTL thermal conductivity model can be used with STANDARD_AIR and IDEAL_GAS" << endl;
1791  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
1792  }
1793 
1794  }
1795 
1796  /*--- Set grid movement kind to NO_MOVEMENT if not specified, which means
1797  that we also set the Grid_Movement flag to false. We initialize to the
1798  number of zones here, because we are guaranteed to at least have one. ---*/
1799 
1800  if (Kind_GridMovement == NULL) {
1801  Kind_GridMovement = new unsigned short[nZone];
1802  for (unsigned short iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++ )
1803  Kind_GridMovement[iZone] = NO_MOVEMENT;
1804  if (Grid_Movement == true) {
1805  cout << "GRID_MOVEMENT = YES but no type provided in GRID_MOVEMENT_KIND!!" << endl;
1806  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
1807  }

1811  movement (both rotating frame and moving walls can be steady), make sure that
1812  there is no grid motion ---*/

1815  (Unsteady_Simulation == STEADY) &&

1818  (Kind_GridMovement[ZONE_0] != STEADY_TRANSLATION)))
1819  Grid_Movement = false;

1822  equal to the freestream value. ---*/

1831  else
1832  Rotating_Frame = false;

1835  types provided (should be equal, except that rigid motion and rotating frame

2156 
2157  /*--- Use the various rigid-motion input frequencies to determine the period to be used with time-spectral cases.
2158  There are THREE types of motion to consider, namely: rotation, pitching, and plunging.
2159  The largest period of motion is the one to be used for time-spectral calculations. ---*/
2160 
2161  if (Unsteady_Simulation == TIME_SPECTRAL) {
2162 
2163  unsigned short N_MOTION_TYPES = 3;
2164  su2double *periods;
2165  periods = new su2double[N_MOTION_TYPES];
2166 
2167  /*--- rotation: ---*/
2168 
2169  su2double Omega_mag_rot = sqrt(pow(Rotation_Rate_X[ZONE_0],2)+pow(Rotation_Rate_Y[ZONE_0],2)+pow(Rotation_Rate_Z[ZONE_0],2));
2170  if (Omega_mag_rot > 0)
2171  periods[0] = 2*PI_NUMBER/Omega_mag_rot;
2172  else
2173  periods[0] = 0.0;
2174 
2175  /*--- pitching: ---*/
2176 
2177  su2double Omega_mag_pitch = sqrt(pow(Pitching_Omega_X[ZONE_0],2)+pow(Pitching_Omega_Y[ZONE_0],2)+pow(Pitching_Omega_Z[ZONE_0],2));
2178  if (Omega_mag_pitch > 0)
2179  periods[1] = 2*PI_NUMBER/Omega_mag_pitch;
2180  else
2181  periods[1] = 0.0;
2182 
2183  /*--- plunging: ---*/
2184 
2185  su2double Omega_mag_plunge = sqrt(pow(Plunging_Omega_X[ZONE_0],2)+pow(Plunging_Omega_Y[ZONE_0],2)+pow(Plunging_Omega_Z[ZONE_0],2));
2186  if (Omega_mag_plunge > 0)
2187  periods[2] = 2*PI_NUMBER/Omega_mag_plunge;
2188  else
2189  periods[2] = 0.0;
2190 
2191  /*--- determine which period is largest ---*/
2192 
2193  unsigned short iVar;
2194  TimeSpectral_Period = 0.0;
2195  for (iVar = 0; iVar < N_MOTION_TYPES; iVar++) {
2196  if (periods[iVar] > TimeSpectral_Period)
2197  TimeSpectral_Period = periods[iVar];
2198  }
2199 
2200  delete periods;
2201 
2202  }
2203 
2204  /*--- Initialize the RefOriginMoment Pointer ---*/
2205 
2206  RefOriginMoment = NULL;
2207  RefOriginMoment = new su2double[3];

2421  MG_PostSmooth[i] = 0;

2609

2611

2614  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);

2634  break;

2641

2643  SpatialOrder_Flow = SECOND_ORDER;
2644 
2645  if ((Kind_ConvNumScheme_AdjFlow == SPACE_CENTERED) && (Kind_Centered_AdjFlow == JST) && (SpatialOrder_AdjFlow == SECOND_ORDER_LIMITER))
2646  SpatialOrder_AdjFlow = SECOND_ORDER;
2647 
2648  delete [] tmp_smooth;
2649 
2650 }

2652 void CConfig::SetMarkers(unsigned short val_software) {
2653 
2654  unsigned short iMarker_All, iMarker_CfgFile, iMarker_Euler, iMarker_Custom,
2655  iMarker_FarField, iMarker_SymWall, iMarker_Pressure, iMarker_PerBound,
2656  iMarker_NearFieldBound, iMarker_InterfaceBound, iMarker_Dirichlet,

2671

2673

2675  nMarker_Pressure + nMarker_PerBound + nMarker_NearFieldBound +
2676  nMarker_InterfaceBound + nMarker_Dirichlet + nMarker_Neumann + nMarker_Inlet + nMarker_Riemann +
2677  nMarker_NRBC + nMarker_Outlet + nMarker_Isothermal + nMarker_HeatFlux +
2678  nMarker_EngineInflow + nMarker_EngineBleed + nMarker_EngineExhaust +
2679  nMarker_Supersonic_Inlet + nMarker_Supersonic_Outlet + nMarker_Displacement + nMarker_Load +
2680  nMarker_FlowLoad + nMarker_Custom +
2681  nMarker_Clamped + nMarker_Load_Sine + nMarker_Load_Dir +
2682  nMarker_ActDisk_Inlet + nMarker_ActDisk_Outlet + nMarker_Out_1D;
2683 
2684  /*--- Add the possible send/receive domains ---*/
2685 
2686  nMarker_Max = nMarker_CfgFile + 2*size;
2687 
2688  /*--- Basic dimensionalization of the markers (worst scenario) ---*/
2689 
2690  nMarker_All = nMarker_Max;
2691 
2692  /*--- Allocate the memory (markers in each domain) ---*/
2693 
2694  Marker_All_TagBound = new string[nMarker_All]; // Store the tag that correspond with each marker.
2695  Marker_All_SendRecv = new short[nMarker_All]; // +#domain (send), -#domain (receive).
2696  Marker_All_KindBC = new unsigned short[nMarker_All]; // Store the kind of boundary condition.
2697  Marker_All_Monitoring = new unsigned short[nMarker_All]; // Store whether the boundary should be monitored.
2698  Marker_All_Designing = new unsigned short[nMarker_All]; // Store whether the boundary should be designed.
2699  Marker_All_Plotting = new unsigned short[nMarker_All]; // Store whether the boundary should be plotted.
2700  Marker_All_FSIinterface = new unsigned short[nMarker_All]; // Store whether the boundary is in the FSI interface.
2701  Marker_All_GeoEval = new unsigned short[nMarker_All]; // Store whether the boundary should be geometry evaluation.
2702  Marker_All_DV = new unsigned short[nMarker_All]; // Store whether the boundary should be affected by design variables.
2703  Marker_All_Moving = new unsigned short[nMarker_All]; // Store whether the boundary should be in motion.
2704  Marker_All_PerBound = new short[nMarker_All]; // Store whether the boundary belongs to a periodic boundary.
2705  Marker_All_Out_1D = new unsigned short[nMarker_All]; // Store whether the boundary belongs to a 1-d output boundary.
2706 
2707  for (iMarker_All = 0; iMarker_All < nMarker_All; iMarker_All++) {
2708  Marker_All_TagBound[iMarker_All] = "SEND_RECEIVE";
2709  Marker_All_SendRecv[iMarker_All] = 0;
2710  Marker_All_KindBC[iMarker_All] = 0;
2711  Marker_All_Monitoring[iMarker_All] = 0;
2712  Marker_All_GeoEval[iMarker_All] = 0;
2713  Marker_All_Designing[iMarker_All] = 0;
2714  Marker_All_Plotting[iMarker_All] = 0;
2715  Marker_All_FSIinterface[iMarker_All] = 0;
2716  Marker_All_DV[iMarker_All] = 0;
2717  Marker_All_Moving[iMarker_All] = 0;
2718  Marker_All_PerBound[iMarker_All] = 0;
2719  Marker_All_Out_1D[iMarker_All] = 0;
2720  }
2721 
2722  /*--- Allocate the memory (markers in the config file) ---*/
2723

2726  Marker_CfgFile_Monitoring = new unsigned short[nMarker_CfgFile];
2727  Marker_CfgFile_Designing = new unsigned short[nMarker_CfgFile];
2728  Marker_CfgFile_Plotting = new unsigned short[nMarker_CfgFile];
2729  Marker_CfgFile_GeoEval = new unsigned short[nMarker_CfgFile];
2730  Marker_CfgFile_FSIinterface = new unsigned short[nMarker_CfgFile];
2731  Marker_CfgFile_DV = new unsigned short[nMarker_CfgFile];

2734  Marker_CfgFile_Out_1D = new unsigned short[nMarker_CfgFile];
2735

2737  Marker_CfgFile_TagBound[iMarker_CfgFile] = "SEND_RECEIVE";
2738  Marker_CfgFile_KindBC[iMarker_CfgFile] = 0;
2739  Marker_CfgFile_Monitoring[iMarker_CfgFile] = 0;
2740  Marker_CfgFile_GeoEval[iMarker_CfgFile] = 0;
2741  Marker_CfgFile_Designing[iMarker_CfgFile] = 0;
2742  Marker_CfgFile_Plotting[iMarker_CfgFile] = 0;
2743  Marker_CfgFile_FSIinterface[iMarker_CfgFile] = 0;
2744  Marker_CfgFile_DV[iMarker_CfgFile] = 0;
2745  Marker_CfgFile_Moving[iMarker_CfgFile] = 0;

2755  Marker_CfgFile_KindBC[iMarker_CfgFile] = EULER_WALL;
2756  iMarker_CfgFile++;

4271 bool CConfig::TokenizeString(string & str, string & option_name,
4272  vector<string> & option_value) {
4273  const string delimiters(" ()[]{}:,\t\n\v\f\r");
4274  // check for comments or empty string
4275  string::size_type pos, last_pos;
4276  pos = str.find_first_of("%");
4277  if ( (str.length() == 0) || (pos == 0) ) {
4278  // str is empty or a comment line, so no option here
4279  return false;
4280  }
4281  if (pos != string::npos) {
4282  // remove comment at end if necessary
4283  str.erase(pos);
4284  }
4285 
4286  // look for line composed on only delimiters (usually whitespace)
4287  pos = str.find_first_not_of(delimiters);
4288  if (pos == string::npos) {
4289  return false;
4290  }
4291 
4292  // find the equals sign and split string
4293  string name_part, value_part;
4294  pos = str.find("=");
4295  if (pos == string::npos) {
4296  cerr << "Error in TokenizeString(): "
4297  << "line in the configuration file with no \"=\" sign."
4298  << endl;
4299  cout << "Look for: " << str << endl;
4300  cout << "str.length() = " << str.length() << endl;
4301  throw(-1);
4302  }
4303  name_part = str.substr(0, pos);
4304  value_part = str.substr(pos+1, string::npos);
4305  //cout << "name_part = |" << name_part << "|" << endl;
4306  //cout << "value_part = |" << value_part << "|" << endl;
4307 
4308  // the first_part should consist of one string with no interior delimiters
4309  last_pos = name_part.find_first_not_of(delimiters, 0);
4310  pos = name_part.find_first_of(delimiters, last_pos);
4311  if ( (name_part.length() == 0) || (last_pos == string::npos) ) {
4312  cerr << "Error in CConfig::TokenizeString(): "
4313  << "line in the configuration file with no name before the \"=\" sign."
4314  << endl;
4315  throw(-1);
4316  }
4317  if (pos == string::npos) pos = name_part.length();
4318  option_name = name_part.substr(last_pos, pos - last_pos);
4319  last_pos = name_part.find_first_not_of(delimiters, pos);
4320  if (last_pos != string::npos) {
4321  cerr << "Error in TokenizeString(): "
4322  << "two or more options before an \"=\" sign in the configuration file."
4323  << endl;
4324  throw(-1);
4325  }
4326  StringToUpperCase(option_name);
4327 
4328  //cout << "option_name = |" << option_name << "|" << endl;
4329  //cout << "pos = " << pos << ": last_pos = " << last_pos << endl;
4330 
4331  // now fill the option value vector
4332  option_value.clear();
4333  last_pos = value_part.find_first_not_of(delimiters, 0);
4334  pos = value_part.find_first_of(delimiters, last_pos);
4335  while (string::npos != pos || string::npos != last_pos) {
4336  // add token to the vector<string>
4337  option_value.push_back(value_part.substr(last_pos, pos - last_pos));
4338  // skip delimiters
4339  last_pos = value_part.find_first_not_of(delimiters, pos);
4340  // find next "non-delimiter"
4341  pos = value_part.find_first_of(delimiters, last_pos);
4342  }
4343  if (option_value.size() == 0) {
4344  cerr << "Error in TokenizeString(): "
4345  << "option " << option_name << " in configuration file with no value assigned."
4346  << endl;
4347  throw(-1);
4348  }
4349 
4350 #if 0
4351  cout << "option value(s) = ";
4352  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < option_value.size(); i++)
4353  cout << option_value[i] << " ";
4354  cout << endl;
4355 #endif
4356 
4357  // look for ';' DV delimiters attached to values
4358  vector<string>::iterator it;
4359  it = option_value.begin();
4360  while (it != option_value.end()) {
4361  if (it->compare(";") == 0) {
4362  it++;
4363  continue;
4364  }
4365 
4366  pos = it->find(';');
4367  if (pos != string::npos) {
4368  string before_semi = it->substr(0, pos);
4369  string after_semi= it->substr(pos+1, string::npos);
4370  if (before_semi.empty()) {
4371  *it = ";";
4372  it++;
4373  option_value.insert(it, after_semi);
4374  } else {
4375  *it = before_semi;
4376  it++;
4377  vector<string> to_insert;
4378  to_insert.push_back(";");
4379  if (!after_semi.empty())
4380  to_insert.push_back(after_semi);
4381  option_value.insert(it, to_insert.begin(), to_insert.end());
4382  }
4383  it = option_value.begin(); // go back to beginning; not efficient
4384  continue;
4385  } else {
4386  it++;
4387  }
4388  }
4389 #if 0
4390  cout << "option value(s) = ";
4391  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < option_value.size(); i++)
4392  cout << option_value[i] << " ";
4393  cout << endl;
4394 #endif
4395  // remove any consecutive ";"
4396  it = option_value.begin();
4397  bool semi_at_prev = false;
4398  while (it != option_value.end()) {
4399  if (semi_at_prev) {
4400  if (it->compare(";") == 0) {
4401  option_value.erase(it);
4402  it = option_value.begin();
4403  semi_at_prev = false;
4404  continue;
4405  }
4406  }
4407  if (it->compare(";") == 0) {
4408  semi_at_prev = true;
4409  } else {
4410  semi_at_prev = false;
4411  }
4412  it++;
4413  }
4414 
4415 #if 0
4416  cout << "option value(s) = ";
4417  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < option_value.size(); i++)
4418  cout << option_value[i] << " ";
4419  cout << endl;
4420 #endif
4421  return true;
4422 }
4423 
4424 unsigned short CConfig::GetMarker_CfgFile_TagBound(string val_marker) {
4425 
4426  unsigned short iMarker_CfgFile;
4427 
4428  for (iMarker_CfgFile = 0; iMarker_CfgFile < nMarker_CfgFile; iMarker_CfgFile++)
4429  if (Marker_CfgFile_TagBound[iMarker_CfgFile] == val_marker)
4430  return iMarker_CfgFile;
4431 
4432  cout <<"The configuration file doesn't have any definition for marker "<< val_marker <<"!!" << endl;
4433  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
4434 
4435 }

4462 unsigned short CConfig::GetMarker_CfgFile_Designing(string val_marker) {
4463  unsigned short iMarker_CfgFile;
4464  for (iMarker_CfgFile = 0; iMarker_CfgFile < nMarker_CfgFile; iMarker_CfgFile++)

4691 string CConfig::GetUnsteady_FileName(string val_filename, int val_iter) {
4692 
4693  string UnstExt, UnstFilename = val_filename;
4694  char buffer[50];
4695 
4696  /*--- Check that a positive value iteration is requested (for now). ---*/
4697 
4698  if (val_iter < 0) {
4699  cout << "Requesting a negative iteration number for the restart file!!" << endl;
4700  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
4701  }
4702 
4703  /*--- Append iteration number for unsteady cases ---*/
4704  if ((Wrt_Unsteady) || (Unsteady_Simulation == TIME_SPECTRAL) || (Wrt_Dynamic)) {
4705  unsigned short lastindex = UnstFilename.find_last_of(".");
4706  UnstFilename = UnstFilename.substr(0, lastindex);
4707  if ((val_iter >= 0) && (val_iter < 10)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_0000%d.dat", val_iter);
4708  if ((val_iter >= 10) && (val_iter < 100)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_000%d.dat", val_iter);
4709  if ((val_iter >= 100) && (val_iter < 1000)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_00%d.dat", val_iter);
4710  if ((val_iter >= 1000) && (val_iter < 10000)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_0%d.dat", val_iter);
4711  if (val_iter >= 10000) SPRINTF (buffer, "_%d.dat", val_iter);
4712  string UnstExt = string(buffer);
4713  UnstFilename.append(UnstExt);
4714  }
4715 
4716  return UnstFilename;
4717 }
4718 
4719 string CConfig::GetMultizone_FileName(string val_filename, int val_iZone) {
4720 
4721  string multizone_filename = val_filename;
4722  char buffer[50];
4723 
4724  if (GetnZone() > 1){
4725  unsigned short lastindex = multizone_filename.find_last_of(".");
4726  multizone_filename = multizone_filename.substr(0, lastindex);
4727  SPRINTF (buffer, "_%d.dat", SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone));
4728  multizone_filename.append(string(buffer));
4729  }
4730 
4731  return multizone_filename;
4732 }

4734 string CConfig::GetObjFunc_Extension(string val_filename) {
4735 
4736  string AdjExt, Filename = val_filename;
4737 
4738  if (ContinuousAdjoint || DiscreteAdjoint) {
4739 
4740  /*--- Remove filename extension (.dat) ---*/
4741  unsigned short lastindex = Filename.find_last_of(".");
4742  Filename = Filename.substr(0, lastindex);
4743 
4744  switch (Kind_ObjFunc) {
4745  case DRAG_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cd"; break;
4746  case LIFT_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cl"; break;
4747  case SIDEFORCE_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_csf"; break;
4748  case INVERSE_DESIGN_PRESSURE: AdjExt = "_invpress"; break;
4749  case INVERSE_DESIGN_HEATFLUX: AdjExt = "_invheat"; break;
4750  case MOMENT_X_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cmx"; break;
4751  case MOMENT_Y_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cmy"; break;
4752  case MOMENT_Z_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cmz"; break;
4753  case EFFICIENCY: AdjExt = "_eff"; break;
4754  case EQUIVALENT_AREA: AdjExt = "_ea"; break;
4755  case NEARFIELD_PRESSURE: AdjExt = "_nfp"; break;
4756  case FORCE_X_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cfx"; break;
4757  case FORCE_Y_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cfy"; break;
4758  case FORCE_Z_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cfz"; break;
4759  case THRUST_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_ct"; break;
4760  case TORQUE_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cq"; break;
4761  case TOTAL_HEATFLUX: AdjExt = "_totheat"; break;
4762  case MAXIMUM_HEATFLUX: AdjExt = "_maxheat"; break;
4763  case FIGURE_OF_MERIT: AdjExt = "_merit"; break;
4764  case FREE_SURFACE: AdjExt = "_fs"; break;
4765  case AVG_TOTAL_PRESSURE: AdjExt = "_pt"; break;
4766  case AVG_OUTLET_PRESSURE: AdjExt = "_pe"; break;
4767  case MASS_FLOW_RATE: AdjExt = "_mfr"; break;
4768  case OUTFLOW_GENERALIZED: AdjExt = "_chn"; break;
4769  }
4770  Filename.append(AdjExt);
4771 
4772  /*--- Lastly, add the .dat extension ---*/
4773  Filename.append(".dat");
4774 
4775  }
4776 
4777  return Filename;
4778 }

4810 void CConfig::SetGlobalParam(unsigned short val_solver,
4811  unsigned short val_system,
4812  unsigned long val_extiter) {
4813 
4814  /*--- Set the simulation global time ---*/
4815  Current_UnstTime = static_cast<su2double>(val_extiter)*Delta_UnstTime;
4816  Current_UnstTimeND = static_cast<su2double>(val_extiter)*Delta_UnstTimeND;
4817 
4818  /*--- Set the solver methods ---*/
4819  switch (val_solver) {
4820  case EULER:
4821  if (val_system == RUNTIME_FLOW_SYS) {
4822  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Flow, Kind_Centered_Flow,
4823  Kind_Upwind_Flow, Kind_SlopeLimit_Flow,
4824  SpatialOrder_Flow);
4825  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Flow);
4826  }
4827  break;
4828  case NAVIER_STOKES:
4829  if (val_system == RUNTIME_FLOW_SYS) {
4830  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Flow, Kind_Centered_Flow,
4831  Kind_Upwind_Flow, Kind_SlopeLimit_Flow,
4832  SpatialOrder_Flow);
4833  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Flow);
4834  }
4835  break;
4836  case RANS:
4837  if (val_system == RUNTIME_FLOW_SYS) {
4838  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Flow, Kind_Centered_Flow,
4839  Kind_Upwind_Flow, Kind_SlopeLimit_Flow,
4840  SpatialOrder_Flow);
4841  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Flow);
4842  }
4843  if (val_system == RUNTIME_TURB_SYS) {
4844  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Turb, Kind_Centered_Turb,
4845  Kind_Upwind_Turb, Kind_SlopeLimit_Turb,
4846  SpatialOrder_Turb);
4847  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Turb);
4848  }
4849  if (val_system == RUNTIME_TRANS_SYS) {
4850  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Turb, Kind_Centered_Turb,
4851  Kind_Upwind_Turb, Kind_SlopeLimit_Turb,
4852  SpatialOrder_Turb);
4853  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Turb);
4854  }
4855  break;
4856  case ADJ_EULER:
4857  if (val_system == RUNTIME_FLOW_SYS) {
4858  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Flow, Kind_Centered_Flow,
4859  Kind_Upwind_Flow, Kind_SlopeLimit_Flow,
4860  SpatialOrder_Flow);
4861  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Flow);
4862  }
4863  if (val_system == RUNTIME_ADJFLOW_SYS) {
4864  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_AdjFlow, Kind_Centered_AdjFlow,
4865  Kind_Upwind_AdjFlow, Kind_SlopeLimit_AdjFlow,
4866  SpatialOrder_AdjFlow);
4867  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_AdjFlow);
4868  }
4869  break;
4870  case ADJ_NAVIER_STOKES:
4871  if (val_system == RUNTIME_FLOW_SYS) {
4872  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Flow, Kind_Centered_Flow,
4873  Kind_Upwind_Flow, Kind_SlopeLimit_Flow,
4874  SpatialOrder_Flow);
4875  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Flow);
4876  }
4877  if (val_system == RUNTIME_ADJFLOW_SYS) {
4878  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_AdjFlow, Kind_Centered_AdjFlow,
4879  Kind_Upwind_AdjFlow, Kind_SlopeLimit_AdjFlow,
4880  SpatialOrder_AdjFlow);
4881  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_AdjFlow);
4882  }
4883  break;
4884  case ADJ_RANS:
4885  if (val_system == RUNTIME_FLOW_SYS) {
4886  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Flow, Kind_Centered_Flow,
4887  Kind_Upwind_Flow, Kind_SlopeLimit_Flow,
4888  SpatialOrder_Flow);
4889  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Flow);
4890  }
4891  if (val_system == RUNTIME_ADJFLOW_SYS) {
4892  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_AdjFlow, Kind_Centered_AdjFlow,
4893  Kind_Upwind_AdjFlow, Kind_SlopeLimit_AdjFlow,
4894  SpatialOrder_AdjFlow);
4895  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_AdjFlow);
4896  }
4897  if (val_system == RUNTIME_TURB_SYS) {
4898  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Turb, Kind_Centered_Turb,
4899  Kind_Upwind_Turb, Kind_SlopeLimit_Turb,
4900  SpatialOrder_Turb);
4901  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Turb);
4902  }
4903  if (val_system == RUNTIME_ADJTURB_SYS) {
4904  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_AdjTurb, Kind_Centered_AdjTurb,
4905  Kind_Upwind_AdjTurb, Kind_SlopeLimit_AdjTurb,
4906  SpatialOrder_AdjTurb);
4907  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_AdjTurb);
4908  }
4909  break;
4910  case POISSON_EQUATION:
4911  if (val_system == RUNTIME_POISSON_SYS) {
4912  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(NONE, NONE, NONE, NONE, NONE);
4913  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Poisson);
4914  }
4915  break;
4916  case WAVE_EQUATION:
4917  if (val_system == RUNTIME_WAVE_SYS) {
4918  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(NONE, NONE, NONE, NONE, NONE);
4919  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Wave);
4920  }
4921  break;
4922  case HEAT_EQUATION:
4923  if (val_system == RUNTIME_HEAT_SYS) {
4924  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(NONE, NONE, NONE, NONE, NONE);
4925  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Heat);
4926  }
4927  break;
4928  case FEM_ELASTICITY:
4929 
4930  Current_DynTime = static_cast<su2double>(val_extiter)*Delta_DynTime;
4931 
4932  if (val_system == RUNTIME_FEA_SYS) {
4933  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(NONE, NONE, NONE, NONE, NONE);
4934  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_FEA);
4935  }
4936  break;
4937  }
4938 }

4961 unsigned short CConfig::GetMarker_Periodic_Donor(string val_marker) {
4962  unsigned short iMarker_PerBound, jMarker_PerBound, kMarker_All;
4963 
4964  /*--- Find the marker for this periodic boundary. ---*/
4965  for (iMarker_PerBound = 0; iMarker_PerBound < nMarker_PerBound; iMarker_PerBound++)
4966  if (Marker_PerBound[iMarker_PerBound] == val_marker) break;
4967 
4968  /*--- Find corresponding donor. ---*/
4969  for (jMarker_PerBound = 0; jMarker_PerBound < nMarker_PerBound; jMarker_PerBound++)
4970  if (Marker_PerBound[jMarker_PerBound] == Marker_PerDonor[iMarker_PerBound]) break;
4971 
4972  /*--- Find and return global marker index for donor boundary. ---*/
4973  for (kMarker_All = 0; kMarker_All < nMarker_CfgFile; kMarker_All++)
4974  if (Marker_PerBound[jMarker_PerBound] == Marker_All_TagBound[kMarker_All]) break;
4975 
4976  return kMarker_All;
4977 }

5369 void CConfig::SetSpline(vector<su2double> &x, vector<su2double> &y, unsigned long n, su2double yp1, su2double ypn, vector<su2double> &y2) {
5370  unsigned long i, k;
5371  su2double p, qn, sig, un, *u;
5372 
5373  u = new su2double [n];
5374 
5375  if (yp1 > 0.99e30) // The lower boundary condition is set either to be "nat
5376  y2[0]=u[0]=0.0; // -ural"
5377  else { // or else to have a specified first derivative.
5378  y2[0] = -0.5;
5379  u[0]=(3.0/(x[1]-x[0]))*((y[1]-y[0])/(x[1]-x[0])-yp1);
5380  }
5381 
5382  for (i=2; i<=n-1; i++) { // This is the decomposition loop of the tridiagonal al-
5383  sig=(x[i-1]-x[i-2])/(x[i]-x[i-2]); // gorithm. y2 and u are used for tem-
5384  p=sig*y2[i-2]+2.0; // porary storage of the decomposed
5385  y2[i-1]=(sig-1.0)/p; // factors.
5386  u[i-1]=(y[i]-y[i-1])/(x[i]-x[i-1]) - (y[i-1]-y[i-2])/(x[i-1]-x[i-2]);
5387  u[i-1]=(6.0*u[i-1]/(x[i]-x[i-2])-sig*u[i-2])/p;
5388  }
5389 
5390  if (ypn > 0.99e30) // The upper boundary condition is set either to be
5391  qn=un=0.0; // "natural"
5392  else { // or else to have a specified first derivative.
5393  qn=0.5;
5394  un=(3.0/(x[n-1]-x[n-2]))*(ypn-(y[n-1]-y[n-2])/(x[n-1]-x[n-2]));
5395  }
5396  y2[n-1]=(un-qn*u[n-2])/(qn*y2[n-2]+1.0);
5397  for (k=n-1; k>=1; k--) // This is the backsubstitution loop of the tridiagonal
5398  y2[k-1]=y2[k-1]*y2[k]+u[k-1]; // algorithm.
5399 
5400  delete[] u;
5401 
5402 }
5403 
5404 su2double CConfig::GetSpline(vector<su2double>&xa, vector<su2double>&ya, vector<su2double>&y2a, unsigned long n, su2double x) {
5405  unsigned long klo, khi, k;
5406  su2double h, b, a, y;
5407 
5408  klo=1; // We will find the right place in the table by means of
5409  khi=n; // bisection. This is optimal if sequential calls to this
5410  while (khi-klo > 1) { // routine are at random values of x. If sequential calls
5411  k=(khi+klo) >> 1; // are in order, and closely spaced, one would do better
5412  if (xa[k-1] > x) khi=k; // to store previous values of klo and khi and test if
5413  else klo=k; // they remain appropriate on the next call.
5414  } // klo and khi now bracket the input value of x
5415  h=xa[khi-1]-xa[klo-1];
5416  if (h == 0.0) cout << "Bad xa input to routine splint" << endl; // The xa’s must be dis-
5417  a=(xa[khi-1]-x)/h; // tinct.
5418  b=(x-xa[klo-1])/h; // Cubic spline polynomial is now evaluated.
5419  y=a*ya[klo-1]+b*ya[khi-1]+((a*a*a-a)*y2a[klo-1]+(b*b*b-b)*y2a[khi-1])*(h*h)/6.0;
5420 
5421  return y;
5422 }

CConfig::SetSpline
void SetSpline(vector< su2double > &x, vector< su2double > &y, unsigned long n, su2double yp1, su2double ypn, vector< su2double > &y2)
Given arrays x[1..n] and y[1..n] containing a tabulated function, i.e., yi = f(xi), with x1 < x2 < . . . < xN , and given values yp1 and ypn for the first derivative of the interpolating function at points 1 and n, respectively, this routine returns an array y2[1..n] that contains the second derivatives of the interpolating function at the tabulated points xi. If yp1 and/or ypn are equal to 1 × 1030 or larger, the routine is signaled to set the corresponding boundary condition for a natural spline, with zero second derivative on that boundary. Numerical Recipes: The Art of Scientific Computing, Third Edition in C++.
